                                                                <div data-widget-id="wid__text__5f4e4cee46468" class="moto-widget moto-widget-text moto-preset-default  moto-spacing-top-small moto-spacing-right-auto moto-spacing-bottom-large moto-spacing-left-auto  " data-widget="text" data-preset="default" data-spacing="sala" data-visible-on="mobile-v" data-animation="">
                                                                    <div class="moto-widget-text-content moto-widget-text-editable">
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“Watch, STAND fast in the faith, be brave, be strong.”
                                                                            <b>I Corinthians 16:13 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“For I am not ashamed of the gospel of Christ, for it is the power of God to salvation for everyone who believes, for the Jew first and also for the Greek. For in it the righteousness of God is revealed from faith to faith; as it is written, “The just shall live by faith.””
                                                                            <b>Romans 1:16-17 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“Put on the whole armor of God, that you may be able to STAND against the wiles of the devil.”
                                                                            <b>Ephesians 6:11 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“Therefore take up the whole armor of God, that you may be able to WITHSTAND in the evil day, and having done all, to STAND.”
                                                                            <b>Ephesians 6:13 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“STAND therefore, having girded your waist with truth, having put on the breastplate of righteousness,”
                                                                            <b>Ephesians 6:14 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">We began with the Belt of Truth...we are committed to knowing truth...we are committed to the application of truth...and committed to executing truth as we face the daily battle of STANDING for Christ in this dark sinful world.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Then we applied the Breastplate of Righteousness which covers the areas most vulnerable, the internal organs and most importantly the heart.  As a person when the realization they are a sinner in need of a savior come to Christ they say, “Lord Jesus, come into my heart”...He desires every chamber of our hearts, no other should have residence...our life is to be “set apart,” consecrated unto Him.
                                                                            He calls us to shed the darkness and live a life of holiness.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Therefore we are brought to “having our feet shod with the preparation of the Gospel of peace.”  The soldiers foot covering.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">We have shoes for every different occasion and many varieties.  On a daily basis our feet would take quite a bit of abuse if we wore the wrong shoes for the task at hand.  We wouldn’t wear sandals in the snow, nor heals to go hiking.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Going into battle one’s feet must be shod with the preparation of the gospel of peace.  Our footing need be sure.
                                                                            Preparation means “having a prepared foundation.”
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">We STAND in Christ and what He accomplished on the cross, He said, “It is finished,” redemption complete.  The resurrection signifies we are justified before God as said in  Romans 4:25; death has been defeated as in 1 Corinthians 15:55-57; and the Gospel proven true as in <b>1 Corinthians 15:14, 17-19</b>.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Again in our journey may we revisit the narration of the Garden of Eden.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“And I will put enmity Between you and the woman, And between your seed and her Seed; He shall bruise your head, And you shall bruise His heel.””
                                                                        <b>Genesis 3:15 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Satan’s plan has been to kill, steal and destroy from the very beginning, not realizing he was playing right into the hand of Almighty God.  In this discourse our Father told Satan exactly what was was to take place.  A state of war played out before all, Jesus will put on humanity in that you will bruise His heel (notice the heal is on the foot).  He shall bruise your head.  Satan schemed using all in his arsenal to bring Christ down.  He might have celebrated when Jesus said, “It is finished,” not knowing mankind now was redeemed.  Then to add to this mortal blow to Satan’s head the glorious resurrection, death has been defeated and the Gospel  STANDS true.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">This state of war that began in the garden of Eden has been won.  Today Christian we STAND in truth, righteous before God Almighty clothed in Christ with complete confidence of all He has done.  The same power that raised Christ from death is available to us today.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10"><b>Ephesians 6:11</b> tells us that we put on the armor of God to be able to STAND against the wiles of the enemy. Verse 13 says to WITHSTAND in the evil day, and having done all to STAND. Verse 14 begins with STAND therefore...the instruction is to STAND bravely resisting, face to face against our adversary, Standing ones ground.  STANDING fast in the faith, being brave and strong.  Jesus Christ our Lord’s bruised heel gives us this right, our feet shod with the Gospel of Peace.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Father today may we realized Your plan for mankind has been put into motion and nothing can come against Your will.  We have no need to fear our enemy for You have called us to serve in Your army, and You equip us  for the battle at hand .  Let us trust as You have the complete victory, and we need only to STAND in that victory.  In Jesus Name...
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                    </div>
